author: Stephen Morey
notes: Morey, Stephen. 2005. The Tai languages of Assam: a grammar and texts. Canberra: Pacific Linguistics.Tai Phake is spoken by perhaps more than 2,000 speakers in Dibrugarh and Tinsukia districts of Assam, India. The variant given in Morey (2005) is from Namphakey village, Dibrugarh district, Assam, India.
